ange the world to make it a better place or make it safer or to get us to the moon… It shows how things can become quite surprising when it comes to science – including a chapter called ‘avoid being boiled alive’”\" width=\"782\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>How to Change the World</strong><strong> by Isabel Thomas, illustrated by Esme Lonsdale<br></strong><br>The judges said: “We love this book because it’s a book about the future and it encourages curiosity and thinking for yourself. It’s about how the reader of this book can learn from what’s gone before, what other scientists have achieved and asks how you might change the world to make it a better place or make it safer or to get us to the moon… It shows how things can become quite surprising when it comes to science – including a chapter called ‘avoid being boiled alive’”</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"594beb2e81dd3402934fe73c6b7ae1bcc726ab21\"> <img src=\"https://media.guim.co.uk/594beb2e81dd3402934fe73c6b7ae1bcc726ab21/0_0_484_559/433.jpg\" alt=\"Author Isabel Thomas.\" width=\"433\" height=\"500\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">Author Isabel Thomas.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"ae94b53bf92f4b46478fb443363122e5b6755499\"> <img src=\"https://media.guim.co.uk/ae94b53bf92f4b46478fb443363122e5b6755499/0_0_2635_3317/794.jpg\" alt=\"Project Body by John Farndon The judges said: “This book about the human body and how it functions is packed with absolutely amazing pictures, illustrations and real life pictures. It has so many facts and activities- this is a great educational book with a great balance between reading and interactive parts.”\" width=\"794\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Project Body</strong><strong> by John Fa